Name: synchronous multifocal osteogenic sarcoma
Definition: A choriocarcinoma of the testis that is characterized by a composition of only cytotrophoblasts and absent syncytiotrophoblastic giant cells.

Name: asynchronous multifocal osteogenic sarcoma
Definition: A choriocarcinoma of the testis that is characterized by a composition of only cytotrophoblasts and absent syncytiotrophoblastic giant cells.
